        "timestamp": "2018-08-21 13:43:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nThis is the original design of OPENO API. It is up to VFC to suggest whether it is mandatory or not",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c27179735111e5ec579244a007423c40332dbfdd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 845,
          "name": "Bin Hu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bin.hu@att.com",
          "username": "bh526r"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-22 15:08:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBecause this is the original design of OPEN-O API and pretty much the same thing as that in Amsterdam (https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/amsterdam/submodules/multicloud/framework.git/docs/MultiCloud-API-Specification-V1.html) and Beijing (https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/beijing/submodules/multicloud/framework.git/docs/MultiCloud-API-Specification-V1.html), I think VF-C is the only user of this API.\n\nI suggest that:\n- The name needs to be \"Legacy MultiVIM API for Backward Compatibility\"\n- The version needs to be V0, because the purpose is really to be backward compatible with VF-C.\n\nEven if we decorate it with \"MultiVIM API v1\", everyone knows it is only usable by VF-C.\n\nWe still have a long way to go to have a real MultiVIM API V1 that is usable by more ONAP components.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
